<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from Mr M</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">Written e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">vidence from</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold"> Mr M. H. Clare</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Executive Summary.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1. Bias in favour of cyclists on the roads.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2. Safety.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3. Training.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">4. Road Craft.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5. Mechanical Road Worthiness.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">6. Regulation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">7. Conclusion.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Brief Introduction.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   I am an individual </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">who has held a full driving licence since the late 1960's, &amp; has had extensive driving experience in the Middle East and Europe including the UK, during this time I have had no cautions or convictions for any motoring offence, or even a parking fine. There</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">fore I feel that I have had sufficient experience to comment on the subject being considered by the Transport Committee.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   I have no opinions for or against cyclists, nor </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">any support for 'Petrol Heads' or other individuals who believe the car is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> king. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ever ,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> there is a growing body of 'cyclist-activists' who wish to claim the roads for themselves. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Main Thrust of Discussion.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Bias in favour of cyclists on the roads.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">    Once again a cyclist-activist has been on TV (Mr Chris Boardman on the Daily Po</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">litics show, Wed 18th Dec. 2013) blaming all cyclist deaths on vehicles. Although it is agreed that city roads tend to be more unsafe than town or rural roads, the blame for cyclist deaths or injuries </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">can not</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> always be blamed on others, and not the cyclist</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> themselves.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   When a cyclist-activist appears on/in the media, there is never anyone from the non-cycling section of the community to counter the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">cyclists</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> claims.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Safety.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">. Many cyclists do not wear safety helmets, Mr Chris Boardman on the Polit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ics Show was not wearing a helmet, &amp; side tracked the question 'why not?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">'.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   ii. A growing number of cyclists fail to have front &amp; rear lights, even in the dark. Even Mr Boardman did not have them fitted, yes it was daylight but it could have started </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">raining.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   iii. Many cyclists do not wear reflective clothing or accessories.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   iv. There is no check or requirement for cyclists to have eyesight tests, or inform relevant authority if they have a medical problem.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   v. Many cyclists carry rucksacks </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">on their back, this makes for a high </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">center</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> of gravity, and more chance of losing control.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Training.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">. There is no requirement for a cyclist to be tested on the 'Highway Code', but motorist are.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">  ii. There is no requirement for cyclists to take</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> a cyclist driving test, unlike motorists. In fact an individual can purchase a cycle and immediately cycle on the road without previously riding a cycle.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">4. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Road Craft.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">. Very often cyclists drive through red lights.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   ii. They also cycle across p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">edestrian crossings to cut through traffic.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   iii. Cyclists think that footpaths &amp; pavements are for their use and not pedestrians. If advised by pedestrians, reply with 'F*** </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Off</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">'. Even in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">pedestrianised</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> precincts cyclists cycle through with the Police </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">just standing &amp; watching.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   iv. More of a problem are the groups of cyclists who ride two &amp; three abreast.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   v. Cyclists manoeuvre without hand signals, &amp; change lanes between vehicles.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   vi. They ride up centrally behind HGVs, vans, &amp; buses and then</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> attempt to undertake from the blind spot.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Mechanical Road Worthiness.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   There is no requirement for a cycle to be 'tested' to insure that lights, tyres, or brakes are in good condition and working. However, all vehicles &amp; motorbikes have to have an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">MOT test.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">6. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Regulation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">. There is no requirement for cycles to be registered and have a visible registration plate. As a motorist, my car has to be registered by the DVLA and my number plates visible &amp; in good condition.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   ii. Cyclists are not r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">equired by law to have a minimum 3rd Party Insurance to cover damage to other vehicles. Once again for motorists this is a requirement.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   iii. Cyclists are not required by law to pay the Annual Road Tax, but are complaining about not enough cycle lanes a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">nd many pot holes.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   iv. Without registration plates there is no way to curb the poor road craft at junctions and make cyclists liable for breaking the Highway Code.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">7. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Conclusion.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Everyday</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> in Chepstow I see one or more cyclists acting as in Para's </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2 &amp; 4 above. In addition there is a purpose built cycle path alongside the A466 Link Road from Chepstow to Junction 2 of the M48. Yet cyclists still insist on cycling along the A466, instead of the cycle path which is clearly marked.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   In Bristol (City of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> the Bike) it is even worse, cyclists ignore cycle lanes, short cut roundabouts using zebra crossings, cycle down roads on the wrong side, &amp; even go down one way streets the wrong way, against oncoming traffic.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   Yes, I am a car owner &amp; driver, and admit </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">that some drivers pull some daft manoeuvres on the roads. However, for any small infringement I am liable for an on the spot fine by Police, for example a light going out during the journey.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Recommendations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">. A National Education &amp; Publicity Programme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> should be implemented to educate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">cyclists</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">, this is ongoing for motorists to be aware of motorbikes under the 'Think Bike' campaign.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   ii. It should be made compulsory by law for cyclists to wear safety helmets &amp; reflective clothing/equipment, and be lia</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ble for an on the spot fine by Police. Obviously persons wearing turbans due to religion to be exempt.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   iii. It should be compulsory by law that cycles are roadworthy, and the cyclist liable to on the spot fines by Police. This to include tyres, lights,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> &amp; brakes, an ideal would be for cycles to have to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">under go</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> an official cycle MOT and be certificated.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   iv. The introduction of compulsory minimum 3rd Party Insurance for cyclists.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   v. The introduction of an Annual Cycle Road Tax for cycles.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Finally.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   Mr Chris Boardman is a poor example of a safe cyclist, yes he is a gold medal winner, but that was on track, during the short film on the Politics Show pontificating about safety for cyclists, he had no helmet, no reflective clothing, no light</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">s on his bike (even though it was daylight, it could have started to rain), and even on TV failed to indicate that he was moving off into traffic. Last but not least, it appeared at one stage towards the end he was actually cycling along the pavement.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">   T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">his is typical of the cycling-activists who rant that vehicles are not in tune with them, but they ignore simple rules. They rant about cyclist deaths, no wants these, but it is never mentioned if &amp; when a cyclist was at fault. Seeing some of the cyclists </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">around, it is a good bet some of these accidents are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">self imposed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>